quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,No! I swear by the Day of Rising
  75,2,No! I swear by the self-reproaching self
  75,3,Does man imagine We will not reassemble his bones
  75,4,On the contrary! We are well able to reshape his fingers
  75,5,Yet man still wants to deny what is ahead of him
  75,6,"asking, ´So when is the Day of Rising?´"
  75,7,But when the eyesight is dazzled
  75,8,and the moon is eclipsed
  75,9,and the sun and moon are fused together
  75,10,"on that Day man will say, ´Where can I run?´"
  75,11,No indeed! There will be no safe place
  75,12,That Day the only resting place will be your Lord
  75,13,That Day man will be told what he did and failed to do
  75,14,"In fact, man will be clear proof against himself"
  75,15,in spite of any excuses he might offer
  75,16,Do not move your tongue trying to hasten it
  75,17,Its collection and recitation are Our affair
  75,18,"So when We recite it, follow its recitation"
  75,19,Then its explanation is Our concern
  75,20,No indeed! But you love this fleeting world
  75,21,and you disregard the Next World
  75,22,Faces that Day will be radiant
  75,23,gazing at their Lord
  75,24,And faces that Day will be glowering
  75,25,realising that a back-breaking blow has fallen
  75,26,No indeed! When it reaches the gullet
  75,27,"and he hears the words, ´Who can heal him now?´"
  75,28,and he knows it is indeed the final parting
  75,29,and one leg is entwined with the other
  75,30,that Day he will be driven to your Lord
  75,31,He neither affirmed the truth nor did he do salat
  75,32,but rather denied the truth and turned away
  75,33,"and then went off to his family, swaggering"
  75,34,It is coming closer to you and closer
  75,35,Then closer to you and closer still
  75,36,Does man reckon he will be left to go on unchecked
  75,37,Was he not a drop of ejaculated sperm
  75,38,then a blood-clot which He created and shaped
  75,39,"making from it both sexes, male and female"
  75,40,Is He who does this not able to bring the dead to life
  76,1,Has man ever known a point of time when he was not something remembered
  76,2,"We created man from a mingled drop to test him, and We made him hearing and seeing"
  76,3,"We guided him on the Way, whether he is thankful or unthankful"
  76,4,We have made ready for the kafirun shackles and chains and a Searing Blaze
  76,5,The truly good will drink from a cup mixed with the coolness of camphor
  76,6,"a spring from which Allah´s slaves will drink, making it gush forth at will abundantly"
  76,7,They fulfil their vows and fear a Day whose evil will spread far and wide
  76,8,"They give food, despite their love for it, to the poor and orphans and captives"
  76,9,´We feed you only out of desire for the Face of Allah. We do not want any repayment from you or any thanks
  76,10,"Truly We fear from our Lord a glowering, calamitous Day.´"
  76,11,So Allah has safeguarded them from the evil of that Day and has made them meet with radiance and pure joy
  76,12,and will reward them for their steadfastness with a Garden and with silk
  76,13,"Reclining in it on couches, they will experience there neither burning sun nor bitter cold"
  76,14,"Its shading branches will droop down over them, its ripe fruit hanging ready to be picked"
  76,15,Vessels of silver and goblets of pure crystal will be passed round among them
  76,16,crystalline silver — they have measured them very exactly
  76,17,They will be given there a cup to drink mixed with the warmth of ginger
  76,18,In it there is a flowing spring called Salsabil